critical_positive: We both had much in common,it seems we were both more liberal. We come from areas that see snow and we discussed what it is like living in that climate. We both like animals and have pets which we talked about.  We both also discussed this year and how tough it has been.
critical_negative: I think what could have worked better was that we were both a bit nervous to start. That’s normal and expected, maybe if we had done more of these it would have helped. We both had awkward pauses when moving from one topic to another. We both also had differing views on mistakes made when younger.

begin_memory_text: We talked about weather in Minnesota and Connecticut, mainly the snow. We discussed driving in the snow and how is affects people (i.e., they freak out even though it's an annual event). We talked about our cars as well.
middle_memory_text: We talked about driving and cars, then drunk driving (I got a DUI when I was 20). We talked a bit about work and covid, and compared how the pandemic has affected us.
end_memory_text: We talked about covid and how much 2020 sucks. We talked a bit about mask-wearing and how it's become such a weirdly political thing, and we talked about odd events in the Michigan political scene.
rest_of_day_open: I think it will go well, I have a day off in two days so that'll be nice (I work six days a week). I'm looking forward to going back to my internship tomorrow - I have a part-time job that I'm not super fond of, and my internship is where my heart lies even though I work for free.
critical_positive: We were both willing to participate and I think there was a tacit agreement to not talk about things that are too loaded - my conversation partner said it was his first time doing this and he seemed a little hesitant. I was relaxed and I think he relaxed a little as we talked, so that made it easier.
critical_negative: We often started to talk at the same time, and I asked most of the questions - at the beginning, I told him I'd talked to my last conversation partner for over two hours and I think that freaked him out a little, haha. He seemed to be a little uncomfortable, and it made things a tad awkward.
